properties.Name: ExperianCompanyProfile
properties.Description: A profile of the company as established by Experian.

Columns.Name: ExperianFileNumber
Columns.Description: The unique and persistent number that identifies and tracks the Experian company.

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp of the Experian profile.

Columns.Name: BusinessName
Columns.Description: The business name.

Columns.Name: BusinessAddress
Columns.Description: The business street.

Columns.Name: BusinessAddressCity
Columns.Description: The business address.

Columns.Name: BusinessAddressState
Columns.Description: The business state.

Columns.Name: BusinessAddressZipCode
Columns.Description: The business zip code.

Columns.Name: BusinessTelephoneNumber
Columns.Description: The business telephone number.

Columns.Name: Bin
Columns.Description: The Experian business ID number.

Columns.Name: ExperianFileEstablishedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Experian file on the business was established.

Columns.Name: YearOfIncorporation
Columns.Description: The year that the business was incorporated.

Columns.Name: SicCode
Columns.Description:
The business SIC Code.

Ex:
PREPACKAGED COMPUTER SOFTWARE - 7372

Columns.Name: BusinessTaxIdentifier
Columns.Description: The business tax identifier.

Columns.Name: NumberOfBankruptcyFilings
Columns.Description: The number of business bankruptcy filings.

Columns.Name: NumberOfJudgmentFilings
Columns.Description: The number of judgment filings.

Columns.Name: NumberOfTaxLienFilings
Columns.Description: The  number of tax lien filings.

Columns.Name: SumOfLegalFilingsAmount
Columns.Description: The sum of legal filings.

Columns.Name: NumberOfUccFilings
Columns.Description: The number of UCC filings.

Columns.Name: NumberOfCautionaryUccFilings
Columns.Description: The number of cautionary UCC filings.

Columns.Name: MonthlyAverageDbt
Columns.Description: Days Beyond Terms (DBT) is a dollar-weighted calculation of the average number of days that payment was made beyond the invoice due date based on trades on file that have been updated in the previous three months.

Columns.Name: HighestDbtPrevious6Months
Columns.Description: Days Beyond Terms (DBT) is a dollar-weighted calculation of the average number of days that payment was made beyond the invoice due date based on trades on file that have been updated in the previous three months.

Columns.Name: HighestDbtPrevious5Quarters
Columns.Description: Days Beyond Terms (DBT) is a dollar-weighted calculation of the average number of days that payment was made beyond the invoice due date based on trades on file that have been updated in the previous three months.

Columns.Name: PredictedDbtForDate
Columns.Description:
The date corresponding to the predicted DBT.

Days Beyond Terms (DBT) is a dollar-weighted calculation of the average number of days that payment was made beyond the invoice due date based on trades on file that have been updated in the previous three months.

Columns.Name: TotalContinuousTrades
Columns.Description: The total number of continuous trades.

Columns.Name: CurrentContinuousTradeBalanceAmount
Columns.Description: The business continuous trade balance amount.

Columns.Name: TradeBalanceOfAllTradesAmount
Columns.Description: The total balance of all trades.

Columns.Name: AverageBalancePreviousQuartersAmount
Columns.Description: The average balance amount for the previous quarters.

Columns.Name: HighestCreditAmountExtendedAmount
Columns.Description: The highest trade balance amount of current continuous trade.

Columns.Name: SixMonthBalanceRangeMinimumAmount
Columns.Description: The six month balance amount - minimum amount.

Columns.Name: SixMonthBalanceRangeMaximumAmount
Columns.Description: The six month balance amount - maximum amount.

Columns.Name: IndustryPaymentComparisonStatement
Columns.Description:
A statement regarding payment comparisons of the business vs. industry.

Ex:
Has paid slower than 70% of similar firms

Columns.Name: PaymentTrendIndicationStatement
Columns.Description: A statement regarding the payment trends.
